post_text:
Parent drop up will start at 8:45 at exit B on 4th Street. Please pull over off of the road and wait for staff. A staff member will scan your qr code which should be placed in the lower passenger side windshield. Your child should be on the right side as well for faster screening IF possible. Please roll down your child's window so we may ask the two screening questions and take your child's temperature. Upon clearance, they will enter exit/entrance B with their mask on.
IF THE SIDE OF THE ROAD NEXT TO THE BUILDING IS FULL, please go around ther parking lot circle and turn right to get in line for screening.
Student pick up will work the same way with students dismissed out exit B after scanning your posted qrcode. No child will be released to walk ups. Please remain in your car.
Thank you for your patience as we try our best to make everyone safe at Schiller Schools😊

Did you miss registration for your kindergartner or first grader? Schiller late registration for K-1st is tomorrow, August 11th at Schiller School from 9-3. Your child must be registered to start school on August 20th. A couple things to remember:
1. Masks are required.
2. One parent per student registering
3. Only kindergarten children will be permitted in the building as they will need to be screened. No additional children please.
4. Even if you plan on your child doing remote learning, they MUST be registered.

CCS District 135
April 17 at 3:39 PM ·

IMPORTANT ANNOUNCEMENT FROM THE SUPERINTENDENT:

Centralia City Schools Family,

The Governor’s announcement today that school will be closed for the remainder of the year is sobering. However, the Board of Education, principals, teachers, and support staff are dedicated to continuing meaningful learning opportunities, food service, and student and family support until the end of the school year. Over the next few days, the administrative team will continue the process of reviewing and analyzing our current Remote Learning Plan. We will adapt as needed and work hard to make sure you are up to date on current information as we have it. Remember to look to www.ccs135.com for all information and updates on our school closure page. I am extremely proud of the way everyone has handled this difficult situation. Your support and encouragement has helped to keep us motivated. Thank you and stay safe.

Mr. Clark
Superintendent
Centralia City Schools District 135

CCS District 135
March 14 at 8:57 PM ·

March 14, 2020, School Closure Update:

After meeting and planning today, our district administrative team has come up with an educational plan, as well as, a breakfast/lunch distribution plan for the upcoming school closure. An informational packet will be going home with all students on Monday.

Please continue to check our social media pages for updates and information. We will be using these pages to relay information as soon as it is released to us. Please note, plans are subject to change as we adjust to new mandates passed down to us from the state. Thank you for your patience and understanding as we continue to try to serve our students’ educational needs as best we can during this time.

*Jordan Elementary, Schiller Elementary, Central Middle, and Centralia Jr. High Schools will be closed from March 17 - March 30, 2020.*

shared_text:
CCS District 135
March 13 at 11:15 AM ·

As we continue to monitor the COVID-19 issue, we wanted to update you on what Centralia City Schools Dist. 135 is doing proactively to stop the spread of any germs:

- We are staying in contact with the local Health Department and state officials, as well as, closely monitoring the CDC website to make sure we have all the most up to date information and guidelines.

- Our custodians and kitchen staff are cleaning beyond their normal guidelines with CDC approved disinfecting cleaners.

- Our buses are also being cleaned daily with CDC approved disinfecting cleaners.

The school board, administration, faculty, and staff of Centralia City Schools Dist. 135 are taking the COVID-19 virus seriously. We will continue to follow all guidelines to help stop the spread of any germs. The best course of action is to keep washing your hands, disinfecting frequently touched objects/surfaces, covering your cough or sneeze, and avoid touching your eyes, nose, and mouth. And remember - stay home if you are sick!

*If your child is sick, please call in to the school and the absence will be excused.*
